The (.log js/console (dom/getElement &quot;query&quot;)) command returns &quot;null&quot; instead of a DOM element. Curiously, manually running the equivalent command in the Chrome console works as expected:<p><pre><code>  > goog.dom.getElement
    function (element) {
      return goog.isString(element) ?
        document.getElementById(element) : element;
    }
  > goog.dom.getElement(&quot;query&quot;)
    <input id=​&quot;query&quot; type=​&quot;text&quot;>​</code></pre>
